<h1>Lunch: Sorang Bapsang</h1>
<p>We drove around the island, and headed east towards the dinosaur theme park. We randomly ended up at Sorang Bapsang for lunch, and had some delicious shrimp stew. The restaurant is old-school (no chairs), which is, as mentioned earlier, really painful for me. But good food alleviates the pain. The lady that runs the place is super nice. And her restaurant has plenty of old-school Korean charm.</p>
